    "(28) Skein subspacesLet C be a finite region.",
    "We define its associated skein subspace byH C:= B C H C 1,(29)whereB C:= f ∈F C B f. As a subspace of H C, the skein subspace H C is equipped with the skein inner product.",
    "The inclusion Σ C 1 ⊂ Σ C induces a map ι C: A(Σ C 1) → A(Σ C): [y] Σ C 1 → [y]Σ C which is well-defined since local relations in Σ C 1 are also local relations in Σ C, and isotopy fixing the boundary of Σ C 1 extends to isotopy fixing the boundary of Σ C. The map ι C is surjective because any string diagram on Σ C can be deformed by isotopy to be contained in Σ C 1 ⊂ Σ C. Recalling definitions (21)(22), defineπ C = ι C • π C 1: H C 1 → A(Σ C), σ C = D -|F C | × ι C • σ C 1: H C 1 → A(Σ C).The normalization of σ C is so that its restriction to H C yields an isomorphism of Hilbert spaces.",
    "The claim about the B f 's now follows by recalling that B f = t f (P 1) and considering, for any two faces f 1 and f 2, the regionC = C f 1 ∪ C f 2.",
    "□ A boundary condition for H C is an assignment p = {p S } S∈Bd(σ C) of a projector p S ∈ Tube S to each connected boundary component S ∈ Bd(Σ C)."
  ]
